Solskjaer: "He's [de Gea] come back focused, really determined, with a desire to show who he is. It's his 11th season and we've never stopped believing in him, and it's important that he also knows that." #mulive [mutv]
Solskjaer: "You know he's [de Gea] a top keeper, everyone loves having him behind them." #mulive [mutv]

De Gea: "I think we reacted very well after the defeat in the Champions League. We were together, we fight until the end. We said in the dressing room we came here to take the three points and we did it, so we are really, really happy." #mulive [mu]

De Gea: "They make the change [Noble coming on as a sub] so it was a little bit strange. At the end, I make the save, take the three points, a massive three points for us, so I'm very, very happy." #mulive [mutv]
De Gea: "It was a bit crazy at the end, a great goal of Jesse [Lingard], a stupid penalty, lucky penalty for them at the end of the game." #mulive [mutv]

Solskjaer: "It was better in the second half and a great response, that was a big thing for me ‚Äì how do you react when you go 1-0 down? It was a very, very good five minutes for us." #mulive [mu] https://t.co/tVbaAPjyIv

Solskjaer: "I‚Äôve spoken about how you can‚Äôt take rests when you defend. We dropped into a back six [for the goal] and there were too many spaces. We were too late to charge the ball. We‚Äôve already sorted that and spoke about that at half-time." #mulive [mu]
Solskjaer: "We have to work better defensively, no doubt. In the first half, we were too easy to play through. We will work on it because there is no respite when you play football." #mulive [mu]

Solskjaer: "We deserved to win. I think we created some big chances, we had pressure on them, should have had a few penalties, great response when they scored, good attitude, very good away performance in a difficult cauldron; the stadium is hard here!" #mulive [mu]

Solskjaer: "The two of them [Ronaldo and Fernandes], of course, have to work together. They‚Äôve played together for Portugal for a little while but, for me, those are top players. Ronaldo arrives in the box again ‚Äì as he does." #mulive [mu]
Solskjaer: "I've seen Mark Noble score so many penalties, you did feel down and out and expected to come home with one point but luckily David [de Gea] has continued his good form." #mulive [men]

Solskjaer: "We are very happy with the win and we deserved the win. We played some very good football, created good chances, we pressed them into making loads of mistakes. Luckily, David [de Gea] saves that penalty at the end." #mulive [men]
Solskjaer: "You're up, you're down, you're up but that's football, you have to live with it and Jesse [Lingard] has learned how to deal with ups and downs in football." #mulive [mu]
Solskjaer: "I'm so happy for him [Lingard] because you know it's ups and downs in football, he was low on Tuesday, now high again." #mulive [mu]

Solskjaer: "Of course we sense the expectations on us this season, we sensed the circus around the Newcastle game. Everyone in Manchester, they have an opinion on football now, which is great, and that's what we want at #mufc - we want that buzz." #mulive [sky]

Solskjaer: "Yeah of course [the fans are desperate for silverware]. That's the ultimate aim, that's what we are here for, that's the history that we have and that's the legacy that we have to leave behind whenever we leave at the end." #mulive [sky]

Phil Jones has since travelled to Barcelona to have microfracture surgery. It involves drilling deep holes into the knee to allow an influx of blood, rich in growth factors, which eventually turns into fibrous cartilage. [@TimesSport]
Phil Jones: ‚ÄúBut I love playing and I‚Äôll do anything for United. If I have to play at 60 per cent and know I can get through it, then why not?‚Äù [@TimesSport]

Phil Jones: ‚ÄúWe always go back to the same point: ‚ÄòOh they‚Äôre footballers, they should be able to deal with it, they get so much money, have this lavish lifestyle.‚Äô But take all that away, strip all that back and we‚Äôre just human beings.‚Äù [@TimesSport]
